# CloudWatcher: Linux Infrastructure Monitoring & Alerting Platform

## Overview

CloudWatcher is an end-to-end Linux infrastructure monitoring and alerting platform built using Prometheus, Grafana, Alertmanager, Node Exporter, and Slack integration.

The project focuses on collecting real-time system metrics from Linux servers, visualizing infrastructure health through Grafana dashboards, and generating automated alerts for critical incidents. The solution simulates production-style monitoring workflows used by Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) and DevOps teams.

